# Adding a Magic UI Component

The Magic UI registry is configured in `components.json` as `@magicui` →
`https://magicui.design/r/{name}`.

## Steps

1. **Install** with shadcn CLI:
   ```bash
   npx shadcn@latest add @magicui/<name>
   ```
   This drops a file under `components/ui/`. Some Magic UI components land
   directly at `components/ui/<name>.jsx`; **move it** to the correct group:
   `components/ui/magic/<group>/<name>.jsx`.

2. **Choose the group** strictly from Magic UI's 8 official categories:
   - `components` — Marquee, Terminal, Bento Grid, Dock, …
   - `special-effects` — Animated Beam, Border Beam, Confetti, …
   - `animations` — Blur Fade, etc.
   - `text` — Text Animate, Typing Animation, Aurora Text, …
   - `device` — Safari, iPhone, Android
   - `buttons` — Rainbow Button, Shimmer Button, Ripple Button
   - `backgrounds` — Flickering Grid, Retro Grid, Dot Pattern, …
   - `community` — File Tree, Code Comparison, Neon Gradient Card, …

3. **Re-export** from `components/ui/magic/<group>/index.js`:
   ```js
   export * from "./<name>"
   ```

4. **Create demos** at `components/demo/magic/<group>/<name>.jsx`. Include:
   - `<Name>DemoStart` — minimal example using all defaults.
   - `<Name>Demo` — the canonical demo from magicui.design docs.
   - 0–3 additional variants if Magic UI shows them (use descriptive
     `<Name>Demo<Modifier>` names — never `Demo2`, `Demo3`).

5. **Re-export demos** from `components/demo/magic/<group>/index.js`.

6. **Add a `<ShowcaseSection>`** to `app/demo/magic/<group>/page.jsx`:
   ```jsx
   <ShowcaseSection
     id="<name>"
     name="<Display Name>"
     description="…"
     docsUrl="https://magicui.design/docs/components/<name>"
     sourceFile="components/ui/magic/<group>/<name>.jsx"
   >
     <ShowcaseVariant
       name="Default"
       exportName="<Name>Demo"
       sourceFile="components/demo/magic/<group>/<name>.jsx"
     >
       <NameDemo />
     </ShowcaseVariant>
   </ShowcaseSection>
   ```

7. **Update the catalog** at `docs/COMPONENT-CATALOG.md` (mark this component
   as installed).

## Anti-patterns

- ❌ Leaving the component at `components/ui/<name>.jsx` after install.
- ❌ Skipping the demo file — every component MUST have at least `<Name>Demo`.
- ❌ Adding Magic UI components to `components/ui/` (without the `magic/` prefix).
- ❌ Inventing a new group folder.
